Subject: Re: Cooling flaps

 >Getting ready to pull the engine out of my 72.

   >It has no cooling flaps or thermostat.

   >Is this something I should try to find and get put back in?

If you search the Type2 archives you will find this is a hot (!) 
topic. Conventional wisdom is that you should have them to reduce 
warm up time and hence engine wear. Some admit that the flaps are 
less critical if you live in the tropics!

HTH

Martin.
